                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Etadanik said: <font color="red"><b>"BoT is a nice replacement for Pyre in positions where every mob is fire immune, and it complements Funeral Pyre quite well if you want to only cast 2-3 DoTs on a mob."</b></font id="red"><br />And if you are on a raid and you cast that on a mob a few times...You'll be summoned before you can say ANBESOL. So to offset the aggro you gotta FD a lot, which further decreases it DPM ratio.  Necro's are generally pretty high on the aggro list AS IS and when a MT dies, chances are you gonna get summoned ANYHOW, but having slightly lower aggro spells can make ALL the difference.<br /><br />I agree with Malarix, make this spell Alteration and LOTS of us will like it AS IS.  <br /><br />Plus NEUROTOXIN is alteration...so don't be telling me a poisionous sounding spell CAN'T be alteration =P.  Conjuration?  Come on, do I CONJURE the blood of thule into a mob?  NOPE I ALTER the the blood in the mob to be more THULE'ish...TOTALLY Aleration.  100% explained...POWER TO ROLEPLAYING =P<br /><br /><b>Deedrok - Arch Lich of E'ci<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=234678" target="_blank">My Gear</a></b></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
